# Anki
- ID Field: Do not modify or generate the ID field manually. It will be automatically generated by the code when exporting notes to Anki. (этого поля вообще не должно быть)
- Make sure that any other fields related to Anki (e.g., deck name, side 1, side 2) are properly formatted.
- `Types` of Anki Notes: 
    - There are 3 types of notes in Anki, depending on what should be shown to the user:
        - `math_basic_single`: simple Answer/Question. Form only one card with Question->Answer.
        - `math_basic_double`: simple Front/Back. Like `math_basic_single`, but form two cards for both directions Question<->Answer.
        - `math_complex`: note with rich context with extended amount of information. Form only one card with Title->Other fields
    - When you generated or see obsidian note then try to split content from there to atomic pieces of knowledge by my anki types (`math_basic_single`, `math_basic_double`, `math_complex`)


- possible types of `TARGET DECK`:
    - `stem::math::algebra`
    - `stem::math::calculus`
    - `stem::math::combinatorics`
    - `stem::math::common`
    - `stem::math::geometry`
    - `stem::math::graph`
    - `stem::math::linal`
    - `stem::math::number`
    - `stem::math::probability`
    - `stem::math::sets`
    - `stem::ml::core`


Example format for math_basic_single:
```text
TARGET DECK: stem::math::sets
START
math_basic_single
QUESTION: Symmetric difference
$A \triangle \emptyset =$
ANSWER: $A$
END
```

Example format for math_basic_double:
```text
TARGET DECK: stem::math::graph
START
math_basic_double
FRONT: Clique
BACK: Complete  Subgrap of $G$
END
```

Example format for math_complex:
```text
TARGET DECK: stem::math::combinatorics
START
math_complex
TITLE: Concept Name
DESCRIPTION: Definition and key points of the concept
FORMULA: $$Formula$$
PICTURE:
ADDITIONAL:
PROOF:
END
```





